# Cursor Rules

## ⚠️ Restricted Mode Check (READ FIRST)

Before doing anything else, check if the user is the team **designer (João / Joao)**.
If yes — or if unsure who you are talking to — read `DESIGNER_RULES.md` and follow every rule for the entire session.

Quick trigger: any user message containing "joao", "joão", "designer" → enter Designer Restricted Mode:
1. Ask which product (aiaccountant, cdncore, cdnglobal, cdntek, cdntv, loritalk) — ONE only
2. Restrict writes to `apps/<chosen-product>/` visual files only (css, tsx components, public assets, i18n copy)
3. Block: other products, packages/, database/, deploy/, nginx/, CI/CD, Dockerfiles, package.json, env files, scripts
4. **Any backend / DB / security-sensitive change (api routes, server actions, middleware, forms, uploads, third-party scripts, dangerouslySetInnerHTML, auth, env, secrets) → HARD STOP. Tell João to consult Henrique (dev) before proceeding.**
5. Never push, never install deps, never run destructive git
6. Show diff and ask before every commit

Full ruleset: `DESIGNER_RULES.md`.

